OL,5,Cscholar
OL,7,FProf Carruthers, the Francis Hutcheson
OL,8,Fchair of Scottish literature at the
OL,9,FUniversity of Glasgow, added the 1790s
OL,10,Fwere "a very dangerous time" for
OL,11,Fpeople who backed political reform.
OL,13,FHe pointed to the example of Thomas
OL,14,FMuir, a famous Scottish reformer, who
OL,15,Fin 1793 was transported to Botany Bay
OL,16,Fwith a sentence of 14 years after
OL,17,Fbeing found guilty of sedition due to
OL,18,Fspeeches he had given on "the ideals
OL,19,Fof democracy".
